title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1985-04-07
lineage: The Master Cassettes were played back with Azimuth adjustment and Dolby B decoding on a Nakamichi CD1 into a Korg MR1000 at DSF 1 bit 5.6MHz. Subsequent conversion to 24/96 AIFF done via Korg Audiogate software. Redbook CDR standard 16/44.1 files were created using Bias Peak, Izotope Ozone's MBIT+ (for all dithering), and Weiss Saracon SRC (all sample rate conversions).
description:
Set 1

Why Don't We Do It In The Road-> Mississippi Half Step-> CC Rider, Bird Song, Dancin' In The Streets, Deal

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, She Belongs To Me-> Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> Truckin'-> Smokestack Lightning-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Day Job

reviews.review_text: Best AUD source To my ears, this seems to be the best audience recording currently available for this show. The others, including the CM tape, are a bit thin, have poor EQ, or are totally bassy. This tape has a muddy low end (bad news for Phil enthusiasts), but vocals sound well blended, the instruments have nice level and separation, and the EQ is more even than on other tapes.
